description.narrative: In 2019, HSS Unit has invested in leveraging strategic partnerships with comparative advantages to address priority financial, supply, demand and human resources barriers hampering the optimum performance of national health systems to deliver on the needs of children. Effective collaboration fostered with key partners Gavi, BMGF, The World Bank (GFF), Global Fund, and HQ/PD and DRP, RO/Nutrition, Child Protection, Education, C4D and Communication & Partnership has advanced significantly the implementation of the regional approaches aiming to improved programme implementation and real time tracking on the progress toward the Child Survival and Development key results for children (KRCs). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
